<TITLE> Masud Bin Momen next ambassador to Italy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 8 (bdnews24.com)The government has appointed Masud Bin Momen, currently serving as a director general for the foreign ministry, as Bangladesh ambassador to Italy, the foreign ministry said in a statement Sunday. Masud will replace the current envoy, M Fazlul Karim, who is scheduled to join as ambassador to Saudi Arabia by the end of July. "I will perform my responsibilities with honesty and sincerity," Masud told bdnews24.com in his office in his reaction. Masud is now in charge of the United Nations and Human Rights Desk at the foreign ministry. Masud, a career diplomat, obtained his master's in economics from Dhaka University. He had also completed a master's degree in international relations from Fletcher School of Law and Diplomacy, Tufts University, US. He joined foreign services in 1988. bdn
